content.description: Easy move to the first bolt onto a mini-ledge. Decking potential above this spot to the next bolt. Reachy move to a small 2" ledge up and to the left with small footholds on slightly overhung terrain. This spot is height dependent (easier if taller than 5'10"). Traverse up and to the right for some sloping, angled holds followed by a pinch up and to the left to gain a stance for clipping the third bolt. Easier terrain for 7-10 feet above to the anchor.
content.protection: 3 bolts to 2-bolt anchor. Rap rings on bolts at the top.
content.location: As far to the east as one can get on the north side of the narrows just before the road forks.

content.description: Easy blocks to the 1st bolt followed by a dieback on thin fingers in a left-facing dihedral. Follow the right side of the flake while clipping on the face. Lieback with smears on the face to access the 4th clip. 2 short mantles above get to the anchors.
content.location: 900 feet down the road from the Rasmussen sign at a curve in the road. Only 4-5 feet between the route and the road so practice caution.

content.description: Balance-oriented start in a dihedral to the first bolt with an undercling to attain the bomber hold onto the next ledge. More delicate stemming followed by thin finger crack that can be used for a lieback onto easier terrain.
content.location: The second climb from the left at the second pullout.

content.description: NOT WORTH IT. Top-rope access is over to the left and along the ridge with loose rock. Choss-fest on shale with loose holds the entire way. Some sketch hand jams on the right. The 20-foot high pillar on the right could go at anytime.
content.protection: 4 pins at the top now backed up by 2 bolts.
content.location: The only climb at the pullout with the parking area completely surrounding a lone tree on the west end of Monroe Canyon

content.description: Awkward thin crimps on an upward and left traveling travers to the first bolt. More off-balance moves on crimps upward to easier terrain above the 3rd bolt.
content.location: The far left climb at the second pullout.

content.description: Climb some blocks to the first 2 bolts. Crimps and a long edge on the right allow for movement up the face to the next 3 bolts. Mantle above the 5 bolt to a ledge. Easy terrain to the anchors from there.
content.location: Behind a large tree on the north side of the road about 800 feet west of the Rasmussen sign.

content.description: Bouldery start to the first clip, then onto slightly overhung terrain but with solid crimps and even jugs. The fingercrack toward the top can be a distraction so stay on the face holds.
content.location: Just left of the sign "Rasmussen Fell Here 1888."
